    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-08T13:00:00-05:00" n="254"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.857 Athenia/116: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-08T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 8, 1939—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Your 25, 7th. Unless by “testimony” in your telegram September 5<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d254fn82">Unnumbered telegram from Galway, not printed.</note> is
                    meant signed statements by officers and American passengers, <pb facs="0296"
                        n="288" xml:id="pg_288"/> it is considered desirable that such statements
                    should if possible be obtained from any of the American passengers who may be
                    available and who have first-hand information whether the attack was by a
                    submarine. Such evidence is deemed essential in establishing claims of American
                    nationals for death and injury resulting from the disaster.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
